window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>My fresh start is finally around the corner—but so is the man standing in the middle of the f*cking road.</b><br> <br> He could’ve died when I hit him, and his two friends are downright furious. But instead of pressing charges, they offer me a deal: work for them for six months, and they’ll let it go.<br> <br> Their secluded mountain estate is vast and beautiful. Full of stolen artifacts and dark secrets.<br> <br> Atticus, Elijah, and Seven might be equally alluring, but they’re also damaged and dangerous—driven by a thirst for revenge they say I can help satisfy.<br> <br> Only now that they have me, they don’t seem to want to let me go. And it’s not one-sided.<br> <br> Before long, their vengeance becomes my own, and I begin to understand that even if helping them claims my life, it’s too late to turn back now.<br> <br> <b>I can’t guard a heart they’ve already stolen.</b><br> <br> <i>White Rose Painted Red</i> is a dark romance full of kindle-melting chemistry and possessive, damaged men who will do whatever it takes to get the revenge they crave and keep the girl they never meant to fall for.<br> <br> <i>*This book contains themes and scenes that may be disturbing to some listeners.</i><br> <br> Tropes:<br> Psycho golden retriever<br> Who hurt you?<br> Forced proximity<br> Damaged heroes<br> Badass FMC<br> Found family<br> 'F*ck it'</p>"; 
